Tourniquet cuffs are segmented based on the product type, application, and end-user to cater to different needs and preferences of the healthcare industry. The product type segment is divided into disposable tourniquet cuffs and reusable tourniquet cuffs. Disposable tourniquet cuffs are designed for single-use purposes, ensuring hygiene and reducing the risk of cross-contamination. On the other hand, reusable tourniquet cuffs can be sterilized and used multiple times, offering cost-effectiveness and sustainability. In terms of application, tourniquet cuffs find extensive use in hospitals, clinics, ambulatory surgical centers, and other healthcare settings. Hospitals are the primary users of tourniquet cuffs due to the high volume of surgical procedures and patient admissions. Clinics and ambulatory surgical centers also contribute to the demand for tourniquet cuffs. Additionally, the segmentation based on end-users includes tourniquet cuffs for adult and pediatric patients, ensuring precise and safe application based on age-specific requirements.

